  <p>Recognizing and managing pain in pets is a critical part of veterinary medicine. At All About Pets Veterinary Hospital, we take a multimodal approach to keeping your pet comfortable and active.</p>

  <h2>Understanding Pet Pain</h2>
  <p>Pets are naturally inclined to hide their pain, which can make it hard for owners to recognize when their companion is hurting. Changes in behavior, appetite, mobility, or temperament can all be indicators that your pet is experiencing discomfort.</p>

  <h3>Signs Your Pet May Be in Pain</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Decreased activity or reluctance to move</li>
    <li>Changes in eating or drinking habits</li>
    <li>Whimpering, growling, or unusual vocalizations</li>
    <li>Excessive licking or grooming of a specific area</li>
    <li>Restlessness or difficulty sleeping</li>
    <li>Avoidance of being touched or handled</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Our Approach to Pain Management</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Thorough pain assessment and diagnosis</li>
    <li>Pharmaceutical options (anti-inflammatories, analgesics)</li>
    <li>Laser therapy for chronic conditions</li>
    <li>Nutritional support and weight management</li>
    <li>Ongoing monitoring and care plan adjustments</li>
  </ul>

  <p>If you suspect your pet is in pain, contact us. We'll work with you to develop a plan that helps your pet feel better.</p>
